content:
I'm here to give an un-biased positive review on this anime and by un-biased I mean full disclosure not based on the ecchi parts but what actually occured on the anime.
I'll be honest, I chose to watch this anime instead of another anime last-minute as a "come back to anime" of sorts. I was expecting this to be like a light-hearted, ecchi anime because it was night and I wanted to watch anime again.
/*   Foreword   */
I did kind of get what I want but the story actually made me want less of it as the story progressed and less it did.People who gave the lowest reviews are slamming the anime mostly for the "bland plot" and the "cliche tits for views" but I think that's based on what's seen from the surface. Sometimes you just got to dig deep to find the good behind a plot. That or I could be digging too much into this. I don't know for sure but I'm pretty sure that what I dug was actually intended to be there as part of the plot.


/*   Full Disclosure   */

The anime in a nutshell as to what you can see, a group of single male perverts in highschool forced one of them to confess to a gal trying to break the repeated system of being single every year and staying a virgin. He does confess and to his surprise they started dating. With perverseness on his mind and the will to lose his virginity, stuff goes on from that point as their relationship progresses yada-yada and then there's your ecchi scenes every now and then.


The thing is most of the reviews just end there albeit being much longer and more drawn out than it needs to be. As I was watching this anime, the characters developed in a way you don't usually see anime characters develop. The extremely perverted group of friends eventually start to mature near the end of the anime. The gal and the guy started understanding how a relationship works including the bitterness and sweetness of it. And the overall plot develops as well. I don't know if other people noticed but as the story progressed and as the characters slowly started to mature, ecchi scenes started to dwindle as "true love" started to replace infatuation. By the last episode there were none if my memory serves me right because at that point the once perverted MC has grown out of his perverse shell and matured into a person who cared for the person he love the most, even sacrificing the attempts of his friends to make him carry out perverse acts. The thing why most people don't see this I think is because the context is brought about in such a light-hearted manner.


My favorite thing probably about this anime is it's not your typical harem anime where every girl seems to have a chance at the main character and the anime drags it on and on until the season ends and no real answer is given, only cliffhangers. To be honest, those anime have really high ratings despite what most refuse to accept is that it's mostly fillers with no real relation to the story except to fuel the fandoms. The story on this anime however, you can connect nearly every scene to the progression of the plot and the development of the characters, not some random events that just happen to look like plot but is just fanservice in reality. This anime finishes the story. This anime made it clear who wins. This anime despite being a harem anime has a set of harem characters who are actually likeable and not being fought as the "best girl" because they could possibly be the one. In the end, the other girls here eventually supported who won despite having feelings for the MC. And all of this slowly grew in the anime, you just had to sift it through the light-heartedness of the way it was portrayed.


/*   Final Notes   */

To end this rant, I would like to say that reviews are just reviews. Other reviews are just their opinions. My reviews are my opinions. If the anime caught your eye in a positive manner even if it usually isnt you're flavor of anime, watch it. Don't take reviews completely as "the ultimate verdict". Despite the reviews, you might actually like it or hate it. Only you can tell because your opinions and the way your brain decides to like things is unique. You might see positivite reviews but end up hating it. You might see negative reviews and miss out on an anime that you would enjoy greatly. Or not. That is for you to decide before, during and after watching. Reviews are meant to give an idea, not a definitive, but a constructive idea.
